featured_reviews.review_translated_text: When you visit this beautiful Jain temple in South East Delhi. You feel as if you have entered heaven, the atmosphere of the temples is so serene and peaceful. That you like to come here again. And there is accommodation facility for about 100-150 persons. The rooms were very big and spacious. If you live here then you will not have to worry about food because there is a restaurant here in which very tasty and satwik food is prepared daily, near South ex metro station.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Jai Jinendra
The temple is absolutely peaceful and beautiful.
With due respect, the dada badi staff needs to be more cooperative and logical. They are very rude and dismissive, even when it comes to providing tokens for meals. They should understand that people can eat outside in any restaurant but if someone is choosing to have satvik meals at the temple bhojanshala - it should be promoted. Their policies are unclear and change for rich/known people. We hope someone responsible will read this post and create a happy/ peaceful environment at Dadabadi.
